---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import CTABlock from '../../components/CTABlock.astro';
import { business, BASE } from '../../data/business';
import { postBySlug } from '../../data/posts';

const post = postBySlug('emergency-plumber-mauchline')!;
const siteUrl = business.siteUrl.replace(/\/$/, '');
const url = `${siteUrl}/blog/${post.slug}/`;
const ogImage = `${siteUrl}${post.ogImage}`;

const articleSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  '@id': `${url}#article`,
  headline: post.title,
  description: post.description,
  inLanguage: 'en-GB',
  datePublished: post.date,
  dateModified: post.date,
  author: {
    '@type': 'Person',
    name: post.author,
    worksFor: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` },
  },
  publisher: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` },
  image: [ogImage],
  mainEntityOfPage: url,
  articleSection: 'Emergency plumbing',
  keywords: [post.keyword, '24 hour plumber Ayrshire', 'burst pipe Mauchline', 'emergency plumber KA5', 'out of hours plumber Ayrshire'],
  wordCount: post.wordCount,
  about: { '@type': 'Place', name: 'Mauchline, Scotland' },
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`${post.title} | Sorn Handyman Services`}
  description={post.description}
  canonicalPath={`/blog/${post.slug}/`}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  extraSchema={articleSchema}
>
  <Breadcrumbs trail={[
    { name: 'Home', href: `${BASE}/` },
    { name: 'Blog', href: `${BASE}/blog/` },
    { name: post.title },
  ]} />

  <article class="container-x py-10 lg:py-14 max-w-3xl">
    <header>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-amber-600">
        <span>{post.area}</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <span class="text-navy-900/60">{post.readMinutes} min read</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <time datetime={post.date} class="text-navy-900/60">{post.dateDisplay}</time>
      </div>
      <h1 class="mt-4 font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-navy-900 leading-tight">
        {post.title}
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg text-navy-900/75">
        What the £60 out-of-hours minimum actually buys you when a pipe lets go
        at 2am in Mauchline — what we do, how fast we get there from Sorn, and
        what you can do in the sixty seconds before we pick up.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose-sorn mt-8 text-lg">
      <p>
        Mauchline sits four miles west of our base in
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/sorn/`}>Sorn</a>. When a flexi hose lets go in a
        kitchen on Loudoun Street at 2am, that is a ten-minute drive for me —
        not an hour and a half from some on-call rota in Glasgow. That matters
        when your floor is taking on seven litres a minute.
      </p>
      <p>
        This is the honest version of what our
        <a href={`${BASE}/services/plumbing/`}>24-hour plumbing call-out</a>
        costs in <a href={`${BASE}/areas/mauchline/`}>Mauchline</a>, what the
        £60 minimum between 10pm and 6am actually covers, and the three jobs we
        will not do in the dark no matter what you offer us.
      </p>

      <h2>First thing: shut the water off yourself</h2>
      <p>
        Before you ring anyone, find your stopcock and turn it off. One turn
        clockwise. In most Mauchline houses it lives in one of these places:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Under the kitchen sink, behind the waste trap.</li>
        <li>In the cupboard next to the front door, low down.</li>
        <li>In the garage, on the wall where the mains comes in.</li>
        <li>Outside, under a small round metal cover near the boundary — but
        that one needs a stopcock key and is the water-board side, not yours.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The second the mains is off, the emergency is over. The damage stops
        getting worse, the clock stops on your flooring, and we can take our
        time doing the job right instead of fighting pressure. If the
        stopcock is seized, ring us — we can talk you through isolating the
        specific line under the sink or behind the boiler over the phone.
      </p>

      <h2>What the £60 out-of-hours minimum covers</h2>
      <p>
        Between 10pm and 6am, our call-out minimum is £60. That is not a
        call-out fee on top of the job — it is the <em>floor</em> on what we
        charge for being out of bed. If the fix is five minutes, it is £60. If
        the fix is an hour, you are paying roughly the same £60 because the
        first hour of labour comes inside it.
      </p>
      <p>Included in the £60 minimum:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Arrival on site from Sorn — usually inside 25 minutes to any KA5 Mauchline address.</li>
        <li>Finding and isolating the leak (stopcock, local isolator, or drain-down if needed).</li>
        <li>A temporary make-safe: cap, compression joint, or new flexi where we can carry one in the van.</li>
        <li>Wet-vac of standing water on tile, laminate or vinyl floors — up to about ten litres.</li>
        <li>Photos of the problem and the fix, sent to you by WhatsApp before we leave.</li>
        <li>An honest answer on whether the fix is permanent or whether you need us back in daylight.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Parts at cost are on top, but most out-of-hours parts are small — a
        flexi hose, a compression olive, a tap washer, a service valve. Call
        it £10 to £40 for parts on a typical 2am burst.
      </p>

      <h2>The three emergencies we handle most in Mauchline</h2>

      <h3>1. Burst flexi hoses under sinks</h3>
      <p>
        This is the number one call. Braided flexi hoses under kitchen and
        bathroom sinks last about ten years. After that they split at the
        crimp and spray mains-pressure water across the inside of your unit.
        The dead giveaway is a fine mist and the sound of running water when
        no tap is on. Shut the stopcock, stick a towel down, ring us. Swap
        takes under twenty minutes once we are there.
      </p>

      <h3>2. Stopcock failures</h3>
      <p>
        Older Mauchline properties — especially the stone terraces around the
        Cross and Loudoun Street — sometimes have brass stopcocks that have
        not been turned for twenty years. When you actually need them, they
        seize or snap. We carry universal replacements and will swap the
        stopcock live where we can, or drain-down and swap if we cannot.
        After, you get a working stopcock you can actually use next time.
      </p>

      <h3>3. Frozen and burst pipes in January</h3>
      <p>
        In a cold January snap, unheated lofts and outhouses around Mauchline
        freeze — usually the last two metres of copper feeding an outside tap
        or a cold storage tank. The pipe bursts when it <em>thaws</em>, not
        when it freezes, which is why the call tends to come in on the first
        milder morning. We isolate, cut out the split section and sweat in a
        new length. Lag everything afterwards so it does not come back.
      </p>

      <h2>What we will not do in the dark</h2>
      <p>
        Three jobs we do not touch at 3am, no matter what:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Full bathroom or kitchen fits.</strong> A tap swap is fine.
          A new bathroom suite is a daytime job with a skip and a written
          quote — ring us in the morning.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Gas.</strong> We are not Gas Safe registered. If the problem
          is a boiler, a gas leak or a radiator that is leaking the hot side,
          we will isolate the water and give you the number of a Gas Safe
          engineer we trust locally.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Mains-side pipework.</strong> If the leak is on the street
          side of your meter or before your stopcock, that is Scottish Water.
          Their 24-hour line is 0800 0778 778. Ring them first.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Response time from Sorn</h2>
      <p>
        From the van in Sorn to a Mauchline address, expect 20 to 30 minutes
        at 3am — the A76 is empty and the lights are with you. In daylight
        traffic add ten minutes. Cumnock, Catrine and Auchinleck are similar.
        For <a href={`${BASE}/areas/kilmarnock/`}>Kilmarnock</a> and
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/ayr/`}>Ayr</a> add another fifteen minutes in
        the dark, more in the morning school run.
      </p>

      <h2>FAQ</h2>

      <h3>Is the £60 a call-out fee on top of the job?</h3>
      <p>
        No. It is the minimum total. The first hour of labour comes inside
        it. Parts are extra but usually small.
      </p>

      <h3>Do you charge more on a Sunday or a bank holiday?</h3>
      <p>
        Daytime Sunday and bank holidays are normal daytime rates — no
        call-out fee in Mauchline, Cumnock, Kilmarnock or the rest of East
        Ayrshire. Only the 10pm–6am window triggers the £60 minimum.
      </p>

      <h3>What if I cannot find my stopcock?</h3>
      <p>
        Ring us and stay on the line. We will talk you through the likely
        spots for your type of house. If we cannot find it over the phone
        we will get straight in the van and find it on arrival.
      </p>

      <h3>Do you take card payment at 3am?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes. We send a Stripe link by text once the job is done. Bank
        transfer is also fine. No cash surcharge, no card surcharge.
      </p>

      <h3>Will you come out for a dripping tap at midnight?</h3>
      <p>
        Honestly, no — and you do not want us to. A dripping tap is not an
        emergency. Ring us at 8am and we will book you in same-day at
        daytime rates. You will save £40.
      </p>

      <p>
        Save the number before you need it. If you are already standing in
        water, scroll down and tap the button.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 rounded-2xl border border-navy-900/10 bg-navy-50/50 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm text-navy-900/60">Written by</p>
        <p class="mt-1 font-serif text-xl font-bold text-navy-900">{post.author}</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-navy-900/75 text-sm">{post.authorBio}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <CTABlock
    heading="Burst pipe in Mauchline right now? Ring Fraser."
    sub="Shut the stopcock, then call. One of us is awake and in the van inside half an hour — or WhatsApp Aidan a photo and we’ll talk you through it."
    location="Mauchline"
  />
</BaseLayout>
